<dl id="n35271c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35271c">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35271c"> 271(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 7 hills / 7 hills</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A small winter stream, named the Lycus, that flows through the promontory from west to south-east into the Sea of Marmora, breaks the hilly ground into two great masses,&mdash;a long ridge, divided by cross-valleys into six eminences, overhanging the Golden Horn, and a large isolated hill <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Hence the claim of Constantinople to be enthroned, like Rome, upon seven hills. <small> &ldquo;CONSTANTINOPLE&rdquo; <cite a>Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 3</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
